<DATE>05/31/2009</DATE>
<AUTHOR>RevMatt</AUTHOR>
<TEXT>Too heavy, too hyped and too limited. Nicely conceived, poorly executed. Drop 600-700 lbs, lower two inches, get rid of the fancy tranny and eliminate the "warranty voided if you use the launch control" and this car could be a world class sports car! The AWD needs some work to improve driver feedback. I sold my GT-R in favor of a Corvette Z06. Nissan developed some great ideas but missed the mark.</TEXT>
<FAVORITE>Great performance for the money! Unique styling!</FAVORITE>
</DOC>
